text: two people made to holler like that
The boys I ’ve picked with when I was young and fair
a grey - whiskered , brown - faced giant with clear blue eyes
the wide - eyed children beside Bess
A man that uses fields an ’ shaws after dark as much as I ’ve done
The Marsh men they call it Dymchurch Flit
A won’erful place for bees an ’ ducks ’ tis too
A won’erful choice place for Pharisees
the reaper goin’ round a last stand o ’ wheat tarrifies rabbits
a crew they desired to sail ’em over to France
the King ’s proud messenger ridin ’ through the land
a Marsh - woman first an ’ foremost
the old boat on the Wall
